, we find very little evidence to suggest a direct causal\nlink between the sources of optical and X-ray variability in PMS stars. The\nconclusion that accretion is a primary driver of X-ray production in PMS stars\nis not supported by our findings.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 4 Jun 2006 22:41:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
